- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper is about post-quantum cryptography and proposes new cryptographic protocols.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper mentions one-way functions and key exchange, which are related to information theory.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the time-complexity class BQP and the hardness of search problems.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the implementation of the proposed protocols on low performance platforms.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the use of combinatorial operations in the proposed protocols.
